package comparatorInterface;

public class ComparatorDemo {
	
	
	/* 1. for  predefined comparable classes like string default natural sorting order already available, if
	 *  we are not  satisfied with that, we can define our own sorting by comparator object.
	 *  
	 *  2. For predefined non comparable  classes like stringBuffer , default natural sorting order is not laready
	 *   available , we can define required sorting by implementing the comparator interface.
	 *  
	 *  3. For our own classes like Student, Employee, customer) the person who written  our own class he is responsible 
	 *  to define default natural sorting order by implementing Comparable interface.
	 *  
	 *  the person  who is using our own class , if he is not satisfied with default natural sorting order , then he can define his
	 *  own  sorting by using Comparator.
	 *  
	 *  
	 * 
	 * 
	 */

